!-------------------------------------------------------------
! H3C Switch Basic Command Configuration
!-------------------------------------------------------------
! Purpose:
! This guide covers essential configuration commands for H3C
! switches including VLAN setup, IP configuration, user setup,
! port management, QoS configuration, and system maintenance.
!-------------------------------------------------------------

!-------------------------------------------------------------
! Step 1: Basic Configuration
<H3C>                                ! User view prompt
<H3C> system-view                    ! Enter system configuration view
[H3C] sysname Netronix-SW01          ! Set hostname

!-------------------------------------------------------------
! Step 2: User Configuration
[H3C] super password H3C             ! Set privileged (super) password
[H3C] undo super password            ! Delete privileged password
[H3C] localuser admin 123456 1       ! Create Web management user; 1 = admin level
[H3C] undo localuser admin           ! Delete Web management user

! Console access (AUX interface)
[H3C] user-interface aux 0
[H3C-Aux0] idle-timeout 250          ! Set idle timeout (2 min 50 sec)
[H3C-Aux0] undo idle-timeout         ! Restore default timeout

! Telnet/VTY access
[H3C] user-interface vty 0
[H3C-vty0] idle-timeout 250
[H3C-vty0] undo idle-timeout
[H3C-vty0] set authentication password 123456  ! Set Telnet password
[H3C-vty0] undo set authentication password     ! Remove Telnet password

! Display user and interface info
[H3C] display users
[H3C] display user-interface

!-------------------------------------------------------------
! Step 3: VLAN Configuration
[H3C] vlan 2                         ! Create VLAN 2
[H3C] undo vlan all                  ! Delete all VLANs (default VLAN cannot be deleted)
[H3C-vlan2] port Ethernet0/4 to Ethernet0/7     ! Add ports 4â€“7 to VLAN 2
[H3C-vlan2] port-isolate enable      ! Enable port isolation within VLAN
[H3C-Ethernet0/4] port-isolate uplink-port vlan 2 ! Set uplink port for VLAN2
[H3C] display vlan all               ! Show all VLAN info

! Create and manage user-groups
[H3C] user-group 20
[H3C-UserGroup20] port Ethernet0/4 to Ethernet0/7
[H3C] display user-group 20

!-------------------------------------------------------------
! Step 4: Switch IP Configuration
[H3C] vlan 20
[H3C] management-vlan 20
[H3C] interface vlan-interface 20
[H3C-Vlan-interface20] ip address 192.168.1.2 255.255.255.0
[H3C-Vlan-interface20] ip gateway 192.168.1.1
[H3C-Vlan-interface20] shutdown       ! Disable interface
[H3C-Vlan-interface20] undo shutdown  ! Enable interface
[H3C] display ip
[H3C] display interface vlan-interface 20

! Enable/Disable debugging
<H3C> debugging ip
<H3C> undo debugging ip

!-------------------------------------------------------------
! Step 5: DHCP Client Configuration
[H3C-Vlan-interface20] ip address dhcp-alloc
[H3C-Vlan-interface20] undo ip address dhcp-alloc
[H3C] display dhcp
<H3C> debugging dhcp-alloc
<H3C> undo debugging dhcp-alloc

!-------------------------------------------------------------
! Step 6: Port Configuration
[H3C] interface Ethernet0/3
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] shutdown
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] speed 100
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] duplex full
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] flow-control
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] broadcast-suppression 20
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] loopback internal
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] port link-type trunk
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] port trunk pvid vlan 20
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] port access vlan 20
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] port trunk permit vlan all
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] mdi auto

! Port aggregation and mirroring
[H3C] link-aggregation Ethernet0/1 to Ethernet0/4
[H3C] undo link-aggregation Ethernet0/1
[H3C] link-aggregation mode egress
[H3C] monitor-port Ethernet0/2
[H3C] mirroring-port Ethernet0/3 to Ethernet0/4 both
[H3C] display mirror
[H3C] display interface Ethernet0/3
<H3C> reset counters
[H3C] display link-aggregation Ethernet0/3
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] virtual-cable-test

!-------------------------------------------------------------
! Step 7: QoS Priority Configuration
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] priority 7
[H3C] priority-trust cos
[H3C] queue-scheduler hq-wrr 2 4 6 8
[H3C-Ethernet0/3] line-rate inbound 29
[H3C] display queue-scheduler
[H3C] display priority-trust

!-------------------------------------------------------------
! Conclusion:
! These commands provide a foundation for configuring H3C
! switches, including VLANs, user access, IP setup, DHCP, 
! port management, aggregation, mirroring, and QoS tuning.
!-------------------------------------------------------------
